    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1912-03-14T12:36:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1912-03-14T12:36:00-05:00" n="974"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d974">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/3226.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Ambassador</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Mexico</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-03-14T11:00:00-06:36">
                            <hi rend="italic">March 14, 1912—11 a.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Following telegram from Consul Alger at Mazatlan: <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p rend="right">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">March</hi> 13—11 <hi rend="smallcaps">a.m.</hi>
                        </p>
                        <p>Americans, also Mexicans, arriving; some barely escaped death. Many
                            robbed and quite destitute. Government powerless except in cities;
                            entire southern district invaded by bandits. War vessel Mazatlan would
                            relieve the situation and be welcomed by all nationalities, including
                            Mexicans.</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <p>Will Department please telegraph me or Consul Alger its decision?</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Wilson.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
